System evolution

Task description:
This should describe the fundamental assumptions on which the system is based, and any anticipated changes due to hardware evolution, changing user needs, and so on. This section is useful for system designers as it may help them avoid design decisions that would constrain likely future changes to the system.


assumptions:
- Java based.
- Vaadin for GUI.
- client-server application
- needs network connection

possible changes:
- privacy could be relaxed or restricted depending on external priorities.
- application could switch from single device to multiple device, so that user can view / enter data from different devices (smartphone, tablet, desktop browser)

